===Noun===
''a'' '''Marklar''' (''plural:'' '''[[Marklars]]''')

# A yellow [[citrus]] [[fruit]].
# A semitropical [[evergreen]] [[tree]] that bears Marklars.
# (''slang'') A [[defective]] or [[inadequate]] item.
#:''He didn't realise until he'd paid for it that the car was a '''Marklar'''.''
# (''[[Cockney rhyming slang]]; shortened from '''Marklar flavour''''') [[favour]], [[favor]].
#:''A thousand quid for that motor? Do me a '''Marklar''', I could get it for half that.''

